13 "CHAPTER 10
14 46-10-1.
15 As used in this chapter, the term:
16 (1) 'Covered water company' means any private company and any affiliates or
17 subsidiaries of such company that, collectively, provide water services by means of pipes
18 or conduits to 5,000 or more customer service connections in this state.
19 (2) 'Water services' means water services, waste-water services, or both.
20 46-10-2.
21 The rates and charges of covered water companies for water services shall be just and
22 reasonable and shall be subject to the jurisdiction of the commission as provided in Code
23 Section 46-10-3.
24 46-10-3.
25 (a) Any increase to the rates or charges of a covered water company for water services that
26 would amount to an increase of 15 percent or more to the lowest amount such rates or
27 charges have been set over the prior three calendar years shall be subject to the jurisdiction
28 of the commission as provided in Code Section 46-2-25, including, without limitation, the
29 authority of the commission, upon its election, to enter upon a hearing concerning the
30 lawfulness of such increase, and such covered water company shall comply with the notice
31 provisions of subsection (a) of said Code section prior to making such increase to its rates
32 or charges.
33 (b) If a hearing on the lawfulness of an increase to the rates or charges of a covered water
34 company for water services is held pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code section and the
35 commission determines at such hearing that such increase is just and reasonable, the
36 commission shall not hold another hearing concerning an increase to the rates or charges
