37 of such covered water company for a period of three years, unless such covered water
38 company intends to increase its rates or charges during such three-year period by 15
39 percent or more to the rates or charges found to be just and reasonable by the commission
40 at such hearing.
41 (c) For purposes of calculating whether an increase to the rates or charges of a covered
42 water company for water services constitutes an increase of 15 percent or more to the
43 lowest amount such rates or charges have been set over the prior three calendar years, no
44 one-time fees or charges assessed by such company for connecting to its water or sewer
45 lines shall be included in such calculation.
46 46-10-4.
47 A covered water company shall keep records relating to its financial condition and profits
48 and losses in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. Such records shall
49 be made available to the commission upon request.
50 46-10-5.
51 The commission shall have the power to promulgate reasonable rules and regulations not
52 inconsistent with this chapter or other laws of this state that are necessary to carry out the
53 provisions of this chapter.
54 46-10-6.
55 The commission shall conduct regular assessments of its jurisdiction over covered water
56 companies as provided in this chapter. When appropriate, the commission may make
57 recommendations to the General Assembly on any legislative changes or revisions to this
58 chapter that may be needed to regulate the activities of covered water companies and to
59 protect the interests of consumers in this state. Reserved."
